
Overview of adj ample

The adj ample has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (8) ample -- (more than enough in size or scope or capacity; "had ample food for the party"; "an ample supply")
2. (2) ample, copious, plenteous, plentiful, rich -- (affording an abundant supply; "had ample food for the party"; "copious provisions"; "food is plentiful"; "a plenteous grape harvest"; "a rich supply")
3. ample, sizable, sizeable -- (fairly large; "a sizable fortune"; "an ample waistline"; "of ample proportions")
